[{"category":"section","location":"#SpectralClustering","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for SpectralClustering.\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.KMeansDiscretization","page":"Home","text":"KMeansDiscretization(normalize_rows::Bool)\n\nIf normalize_rows is true, eigenvectors are row-normalized before K-Means.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.KMeansDiscretization"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.LocalScaling","page":"Home","text":"LocalScaling(k::Int)\n\nLocal scaling affinity where scale depends on the k-th nearest neighbor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.LocalScaling"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.RBFKernel","page":"Home","text":"RBFKernel(; sigma=1.0)\n\nGaussian kernel for affinity. sigma must be positive.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.RBFKernel"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.RandomWalkLaplacian","page":"Home","text":"Random Walk Normalized Laplacian: L_rw = I - D^{-1}W \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.RandomWalkLaplacian"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.SVDDiscretization","page":"Home","text":"Yu & Shi method (Optimal multiclass using SVD) \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.SVDDiscretization"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.SelfTuningDiscretization","page":"Home","text":"Zelnik-Manor & Perona method (Automatic k, cost minimization) \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.SelfTuningDiscretization"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.SymmetricLaplacian","page":"Home","text":"Symmetric Normalized Laplacian: L_sym = I - D^{-1/2} W D^{-1/2} \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.SymmetricLaplacian"},{"category":"type","location":"#SpectralClustering.UnnormalizedLaplacian","page":"Home","text":"Unnormalized Graph Laplacian: L = D - W \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.UnnormalizedLaplacian"},{"category":"method","location":"#SpectralClustering.compute_affinity-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, RBFKernel}","page":"Home","text":"compute_affinity(X, method::RBFKernel; self_affinity=0.0)\n\nCompute the RBF affinity matrix. The affinity between two samples i and j is  computed as:\n\nexp(-||xᵢ - xⱼ||² / (2σ²))\n\nwhere σ is defined in the RBFKernel struct.\n\nArguments\n\nX: Data matrix with shape n_features × n_samples. Each column is one sample.\nmethod: RBF kernel configuration containing the width parameter sigma.\nself_affinity: Value used on the diagonal of the affinity matrix.\n\nReturns\n\nA symmetric n_samples × n_samples affinity matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.compute_affinity"},{"category":"method","location":"#SpectralClustering.compute_eigenvectors-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"compute_eigenvectors(L::AbstractMatrix, k::Int)\n\nExtracts the bottom k eigenvectors from the Laplacian L.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.compute_eigenvectors"},{"category":"function","location":"#SpectralClustering.make_blobs","page":"Home","text":"make_blobs(n_samples::Int=100; centers::Int=3, cluster_std::Float64=1.0)\n\nGenerate isotropic Gaussian blobs for clustering.\n\nArguments\n\nn_samples: Total number of points.\ncenters: Number of clusters.\ncluster_std: Standard deviation of the clusters.\n\nReturns\n\nX: A 2 × n_samples Matrix of Float64.\ny: A n_samples Vector of Int (cluster labels 1 to centers).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.make_blobs"},{"category":"function","location":"#SpectralClustering.make_circles","page":"Home","text":"make_circles(n_samples::Int=100; noise::Float64=0.0, factor::Float64=0.8)\n\nGenerate a large circle containing a smaller circle in 2D.\n\nArguments\n\nn_samples: Total number of points to generate (split equally between the two circles).\nnoise: Standard deviation of Gaussian noise added to the data.\nfactor: Scale factor between inner and outer circle (radius of inner circle / radius of outer circle).\n\nReturns\n\nX: A 2 × n_samples Matrix of Float64.\ny: A n_samples Vector of Int (cluster labels 1 and 2).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.make_circles"},{"category":"function","location":"#SpectralClustering.make_moons","page":"Home","text":"make_moons(n_samples::Int=100; noise::Float64=0.0)\n\nGenerate two interleaving half circles in 2D.\n\nArguments\n\nn_samples: Total number of points.\nnoise: Standard deviation of Gaussian noise.\n\nReturns\n\nX: A 2 × n_samples Matrix of Float64.\ny: A n_samples Vector of Int (cluster labels 1 and 2).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.make_moons"},{"category":"method","location":"#SpectralClustering.spectral_cluster-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"spectral_cluster(X, k; affinity, laplacian, discretizer)\n\nPerform spectral clustering on data matrix X into k clusters. X should be n_features × n_samples.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralClustering.spectral_cluster"}]
